2008-09-30 15:05  olivier.salaun

	* mail_tt2/listmaster_notification.tt2,
	  mail_tt2/listowner_notification.tt2, mail_tt2/moderate.tt2,
	  mail_tt2/user_notification.tt2, src/List.pm, src/Log.pm,
	  src/sympa.pl, src/tools.pl, web_tt2/change_email.tt2,
	  web_tt2/change_email_request.tt2, web_tt2/editfile.tt2,
	  web_tt2/error.tt2, web_tt2/help_admin.tt2, web_tt2/lists.tt2,
	  web_tt2/login_menu.tt2, web_tt2/manage_template.tt2,
	  web_tt2/modindex.tt2, web_tt2/pref.tt2, web_tt2/search_user.tt2,
	  web_tt2/serveradmin.tt2, wwsympa/Auth.pm, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi:
	  [feature] The change_email feature has been rewritten as follows
	  :
	  - using authenticating URLs to check the new user email (instead
	  of collecting his password)
	  - provide an equivalent listmaster feature to change a user's
	  email address
	  - check if user is included ; if so, notify the list owner
	  - rename list member picture if he changes his member email
	  address
	  Also removed old code for the following actions :
	  change_identity, unify_email, record_email
	  
	  New feature to define custom moderation rejection messages.

