2008-05-20 15:22  serge.aumont

	* mail_tt2/listmaster_notification.tt2: [-feature] bettre subject
	  in notification message for list creation

2008-05-20 07:13  serge.aumont

	* src/tools.pl: [bug] fix size limit of list name according to
	  database definition (50)

2008-05-16 15:27  olivier.salaun

	* src/Conf.pm, src/Upgrade.pm, src/task_manager.pl,
	  wwsympa/bounced.pl: [change] no more store unknown bounces in
	  OTHER directories. They are now kept in a bad/ subdirectory in
	  the bounce spool.

2008-05-16 14:30  olivier.salaun

	* wwsympa/bounced.pl: [bug] [reported by H.Rousseau]: bounced.pl
	  would fail to create files in OTHER/ if From contained incorrect
	  chars. The bounced.pl process would loop on these files.
	  Now such bounce files are moved to the bad/ subdirectory.

2008-05-16 11:26  olivier.salaun

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [bug] [#4022]: the anti-XSS mecanism
	  HTML-escape outgoing parameters before web pages are parsed. This
	  leads to quotes '"' replaced with &quot; while editing list
	  parameters. This could break SQL queries for example.
	  The fix consists in unescaping HTML characters in edit_list
	  function.

2008-05-13 08:46  olivier.salaun

	* src/List.pm: [bug] [submitted by A.de Bignicourt, UREC] : fixed a
	  charset problem with custom attributes

2008-05-05 14:06  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm, web_tt2/list_menu.tt2, web_tt2/subrequest.tt2:
	  [change] When subscribing to a list, the confirmation popup now
	  shows up only if no custom attributes will be used; Otherwise,
	  this would require that the user confirm twice : first in the
	  popup, then in the custom attributes form; Also adapted the text
	  displayed in the submission form to custom attributes.

2008-05-02 10:06  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/archived.pl: [bug][Reported by M. Kretchner, INRIA] It
	  was impossible to remove a message from web archvives or to
	  rebuild them. this was due to a regexp to prevent archived.pl
	  from using dot-starting files added by some Linux distribution
	  (as Gentoo). Fixed by extending the regexp.

2008-05-02 08:31  david.verdin

	* src/Commands.pm: [#3990][Submitted by A. Berstein,
	  electricembers.net] The quiet option had been deactivated from
	  the "reject" mail command.

2008-04-30 15:46  olivier.salaun

	* Makefile.am, src/Makefile, src/sympa_wizard.pl: [#3989][reported
	  by M.Deranek][fix] using OPENSSL variable set by --with-openssl
	  configure switch to initialize openssl sympa.conf variable via
	  the sympa_wizard.pl script

2008-04-30 15:21  olivier.salaun

	* src/etc/script/sympa.spec, wwsympa/Auth.pm, wwsympa/wwslib.pm:
	  [#3989][reported by M.Deranek][fix] No more require Net::SSLeay
	  perl module. Using LWP::UserAgent instead

2008-04-30 13:54  olivier.salaun

	* wwsympa/SympaSession.pm, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [fix] session
	  variables were not listed in dump of variables. Now exporting
	  them as a hashref

2008-04-30 12:31  olivier.salaun

	* src/sympa.pl, src/task_manager.pl, src/tools.pl,
	  wwsympa/archived.pl, wwsympa/bounced.pl: [fix] STDERR is no more
	  directed to a file if process run in foreground

2008-04-30 12:30  olivier.salaun

	* src/Language.pm: [#3919][reported by M.Denarek][fix] Error
	  "missing locale parameter" would
	  happen whenever a notification is sent to the listmaster before
	  the current
	  language et set. Now using the default language when set. Also
	  initialized
	  the default language with 'en'.

2008-04-25 14:21  olivier.salaun

	* configure.ac: [fix] AC_HELP_STRING is obsolete, replaced with
	  AS_HELP_STRING.
	  See
	  http://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf/manual/autoconf.html#index-AC_005fHELP_005fSTRING-1639

2008-04-25 14:17  olivier.salaun

	* Makefile.am, configure.ac, src/etc/script/sympa,
	  src/etc/script/sympa.generic: [change][G.Rousse, INRIA][patch
	  sympa-trunk-7-dont-search-for-shell.patch] : POSIX defines that
	  /bin/sh is available on every OS, therefore it does not need to
	  be defined via a variable

2008-04-25 14:06  olivier.salaun

	* src/tools.pl, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Copy_template failed when
	  multiple directories had to be created
	  (mail_tt2/ll_CC for example). Now calling mkdir_all() from
	  tools::mk_parent_dir().
	  Also fixed a type regarding authz errors handling

2008-04-17 06:48  david.verdin

	* check_perl_modules.pl: [Reported by M. Gorecka-Wolniewicz,
	  Nicolaus Copernicus univ., Torun] In some cases, CAS logout
	  didn't work, due to a value of "0" trnaformed into an empty
	  string in the session cookie. Fixed by upgrading CGI version.

2008-04-16 09:27  david.verdin

	* src/task_manager.pl, wwsympa/archived.pl, wwsympa/bounced.pl:
	  [#3957][Reported by O. Berger, Telecom & Management SudParis]
	  When launching Sympa daemons (other than sympa.pl) with an
	  unknown option, the daemon was still launched instead of failing
	  to launch.

2008-04-11 09:38  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [bug][#3947][Reported by S. costard Univ.
	  Haute Bretagne] In the case of CAS authentication, a CAS ticket
	  was requested for any request in the web interface. Fixed by
	  ensuring that the user email is attached to the session.

2008-04-10 15:15  david.verdin

	* src/Conf.pm, src/Upgrade.pm, src/etc/script/tpl2tt2.pl,
	  src/tools.pl, wwsympa/archived.pl: [Change][#3116][Reported by S.
	  Hornburg, C. Cat and M. Deranek]Replacing usage of chmod and
	  chown shell calls by the corresponding perl functions. Usage
	  factorized in tools::_set_file_rights() function.

2008-04-10 12:54  david.verdin

	* src/tools.pl: [#3116] Fix bad usage of ampersands in tools.pl.

2008-04-10 12:36  david.verdin

	* src/Upgrade.pm, src/tools.pl: [Change][#3116][Reported by C. Cat]
	  Adds a new function, tools::_set_file_rights(), that sets the
	  ownership and mode for a file. Also fixed some bugs in the
	  setting of owner and mode for SQLite support.

2008-04-10 09:26  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm, src/Upgrade.pm: [change][Reported by L. Gentis, IUFM
	  Lorraine]When updating a config file while the upgrade process,
	  the "email" parameter value of the "update" paragraph was set to
	  'listmaster'. However, this value was validated against a regexp
	  for emails. this produced an error log, as 'listmaster' is not a
	  valid email address. Fixed by allowing 'listamster' and
	  'automatic' strings in this regexp. 'automatic will be used to
	  designate updates done by processes instead of users.

2008-04-10 08:46  david.verdin

	* src/Upgrade.pm: [#3116]Error in bug fix (bad calls to getpwnam
	  and getgrnam).

2008-04-10 08:13  olivier.salaun

	* INSTALL: added --add-missing arg to automake call

