	  last_login_host_user

2008-02-28 11:09  serge.aumont

	* mail_tt2/moderate.tt2, mail_tt2/sendpasswd.tt2, src/Conf.pm,
	  src/List.pm, src/Upgrade.pm,
	  src/etc/global_task_models/purge_one_time_ticket_table.daily.task,
	  src/etc/script/create_db.Oracle, src/etc/script/create_db.Pg,
	  src/etc/script/create_db.SQLite, src/etc/script/create_db.Sybase,
	  src/etc/script/create_db.mysql, src/sympa.pl,
	  src/task_manager.pl, web_tt2/choosepasswd.tt2,
	  web_tt2/login_menu.tt2, web_tt2/loginbanner.tt2,
	  web_tt2/notice.tt2, web_tt2/remindpasswd.tt2, wwsympa/Auth.pm,
	  wwsympa/SympaSession.pm, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: ***** Replace
	  storage of password with encryption by md5 fingerprint. This
	  ***** make remind password impossible. So now a one time ticket
	  table is created
	  ***** ticket are sent by email as an authentication token. Ticket
	  can be used
	  ***** for lost password, create account, moderation request . It
	  should be
	  ***** generalized to all operation that need a email chalenge.
	  *****
	  ***** sympa.pl --md5_encode_password change password encoding in
	  the database using md5.So IT IS NOT REVERSIBLE,
	  ***** so you should save the database (in a safe place to protect
	  password)
	  
	  - new login method include now "last login from [HOST] at [date]"
	  information message
	  - new daily task to remove tickets older than 10d (task
	  parameters in conf.pm):
	  - purge_one_time_ticket_table_task default daily
	  - one_time_ticket_table_ttl default 10d

