2007-10-11 16:18  david.verdin

	* po/Makefile, po/bg.po, po/cs.po, po/de.po, po/el.po, po/en_US.po,
	  po/es.po, po/et.po, po/eu.po, po/fi.po, po/fr.po, po/hu.po,
	  po/it.po, po/ja.po, po/nb_NO.po, po/nl.po, po/oc.po, po/pl.po,
	  po/pt.po, po/pt_BR.po, po/ro.po, po/ru.po, po/sv.po,
	  po/sympa.pot, po/tr.po, po/zh_CN.po, src/Language.pm: Updating
	  languages

2007-10-11 16:16  olivier.salaun

	* mail_tt2/listowner_notification.tt2, src/List.pm, src/Upgrade.pm,
	  src/etc/script/create_db.Oracle, src/etc/script/create_db.Pg,
	  src/etc/script/create_db.SQLite, src/etc/script/create_db.Sybase,
	  src/etc/script/create_db.mysql, web_tt2/admin_menu.tt2,
	  web_tt2/edit_attributes.tt2, web_tt2/editsubscriber.tt2,
	  web_tt2/error.tt2, web_tt2/review.tt2, web_tt2/subindex.tt2,
	  web_tt2/suboptions.tt2, web_tt2/subrequest.tt2,
	  wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [A.de Bignicourt]New feature: Custom user
	  attributes
	  This feature allows the use of per list custom user attributes.
	  Once defined by the list owner, a form will be presented to new
	  list members on the subscription web page. These custom
	  attributes are either optional or mandatory. The list owner will
	  then see the provided user information while taking the
	  subscription decision. Custom attributes can later be viewed from
	  the review page and editsubscriber page. Custom attributes are
	  stored in a dedicated field of the subscriber_table DB table, as
	  XML data.

2007-10-11 09:14  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [#3377] Fix: in messages composed in
	  wwsympa, URL would be cut after their 80 first characters and a
	  carriage return inserted, thus breaking the URL.

2007-10-11 09:09  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [#3334, #3308][reported by C.Peck, wm.edu
	  and D. Stefano]Fix: dump of bouncers would only return the first
	  25 entries.

2007-10-09 07:53  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm: [#3182][Reported by G. Bouteille, univ. Rennes 1 and
	  J.H. Belpois, univ. Brest] Fix: When instantiating a family with
	  list containing an include_sql_query paragraph, new parameters
	  appeared in the paragraph (db_user, db_host, db_psswd). This was
	  because we used to pass a ref to the hash containing list config
	  values to functions which added values to this hash. We now pass
	  a copy of this hash, temporary values are then never added to the
	  hash finally saved.

2007-10-04 15:13  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm: [#3298][Reported by A. Ma and S. Ikeda] Fix: Sympa
	  would add a "Re:" to each reply, leading to possibly very long
	  chains of "Re:" in messages subjects.

2007-10-04 12:33  olivier.salaun

	* src/Scenario.pm: Fixed the scenario parsing regular expression
	  that did not allow to have a regexp parameter to the match()
	  condition that included a single character

2007-10-03 13:39  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm: [#787][Reported by W. Werner,Fraunhofer SIT] Fix:
	  Two versions of the send_msg() function existed in List.pm.
	  removed the oldest one.

2007-10-03 12:16  david.verdin

	* src/Upgrade.pm: [#3305][Reported by M. Deranek, slonko.net]
	  Upgrade would fail for SQLite databases due to a request
	  containing a MySQL-specific assertion.
	  The test of primary keys and indexes is sppressed for SQLite, due
	  to the lack of a simple way to test tables columns in this RDBMS.

2007-10-03 12:05  david.verdin

	* src/SQLSource.pm: [#3136] [#3319] [Reported by G. Haverkamp and
	  M. Deranek] Fix: Support of SQLite was broken.

2007-10-03 07:58  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [#3363][Reported by M. Deranek, slonko.net]
	  The HTML document date was set to 1 jan 1970 instead of current
	  date, causing some browser to be unable to unlog because they
	  seem to compare cookie date to document date for expiration
	  purpose.

2007-10-03 06:56  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm, src/admin.pm: Fix: When a new Lock object is
	  created, we didn't check that the object tcreation had succeeded.
	  On one occasion, it made task-manager to crash. Now, if the
	  object isn't defined after the "new" invocation, the functions
	  return undef.

2007-10-02 16:03  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm, src/Log.pm: Change: If logs fail, the listmaster
	  receives a message.

2007-10-02 15:43  olivier.salaun

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [reported by C.Wolfhugel] Fix: email
	  addresses containing the '/' character was not properly
	  URI-unescaped, for example with the editsubscriber function

2007-10-02 14:22  david.verdin

	* src/Log.pm: Fix: Sympa no longer crashes when logs are not
	  available.

2007-10-02 12:54  david.verdin

	* src/tools.pl, src/tt2.pl, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [change] Improved
	  XSS protection. Sympa logo not escaped anymore, non escaped
	  parameters and XSS treatment moved to wwsympa.fcgi.

2007-09-28 08:26  olivier.salaun

	* check_perl_modules.pl: Change: require MIME-Tools 5.423. Actually
	  only versions 5.421 and 5.422 would create problems, because the
	  API of MIME::Entity::body() changed.
	  This would make sympa.pl process die with error "Can't use string
	  ("0") as an ARRAY ref while "strict refs""

2007-09-27 06:21  serge.aumont

	* soap/sympasoap.pm: reverse a test about parameters completion in
	  createlist. (reported by Olivier Berger)

2007-09-25 14:28  olivier.salaun

	* check_perl_modules.pl: Change: perform post-install check of CPAN
	  modules. If install failed, first try to force the tests, then
	  suggest a manual install

2007-09-25 09:20  david.verdin

	* .version, ChangeLog, NEWS: Preparing Sympa 5.4a.4

2007-09-24 09:16  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Fix: changes of scenario from
	  the admin web interface did not seem to work because the
	  'selected' attributes were cumulated
	  in %Scenario::all_scenarios. Now only pass the required scenario
	  attributes (name and web_title) to the TT2 web parser.

2007-09-24 09:15  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/Auth.pm: Added comment

2007-09-21 14:08  david.verdin

	* src/Scenario.pm: [#3306][Reported by C. Andrews, boston College]
	  The List::verify resolution of the true test would be applied for
	  all custom conditions that have "true", "any" or "all" in them.
	  Fix: Checks that condiotn starts and ends with the serached
	  condition name.

2007-09-21 12:51  david.verdin

	* soap/sympasoap.pm, src/Archive.pm, src/Conf.pm, src/List.pm,
	  src/Scenario.pm, src/task_manager.pl, src/tools.pl,
	  wwsympa/Auth.pm, wwsympa/SympaSession.pm, wwsympa/archived.pl,
	  wwsympa/chalenge.pm: Removing various development traces.

2007-09-20 15:48  david.verdin

	* src/Log.pm: Feature: Added "trace" log facility to facilitate
	  development messages insertion, visualization and deletion.

2007-09-20 15:13  david.verdin

	* soap/sympasoap.pm, src/admin.pm, src/sympa.pl,
	  wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Fix: info and config files were not
	  properly encoded when a list was created using the web or SOAP.
	  fixed by adding the declaration of origin in create_list_old call
	  and then testing this value to know how to handle encoding.

2007-09-20 14:43  david.verdin

	* check_perl_modules.pl, src/tools.pl, src/tt2.pl,
	  wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Change: XSS protection: Any output web
	  parameter is filtered to avoid creation of XSS vector.
	  Change:Additionnaly, any HTML file put in the shared directory is
	  filtered using StripScripts.
	  Change:HTML::StripScripts::Parser CPAN module is now mandatory.

2007-09-19 06:42  serge.aumont

	* src/Conf.pm: remove unwanted traces

2007-09-19 06:15  serge.aumont

	* src/List.pm: Remove dev traces

2007-09-18 15:05  david.verdin

	* web_tt2/pref.tt2, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Change: Session object is
	  now included in $param hash.
	  Fix: Changing password and email address was no longer possible
	  in WWSympa.

2007-09-17 13:23  serge.aumont

	* wwsympa/SympaSession.pm: fix location of db_connect

2007-09-17 09:14  david.verdin

	* src/tt2.pl: Remove non validated change.

2007-09-17 09:12  david.verdin

	* src/tt2.pl: Removed commented code.

2007-09-14 07:31  david.verdin

	* src/Conf.pm, src/etc/crawlers_detection.conf, src/tools.pl,
	  wwsympa/SympaSession.pm, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Now session from
	  crawlers are stored in sessiontable. Crawler detection is
	  controled by /etc/crawlers_detection.conf.
	  
	  Currently this file only list user_agent strings. In the futur it
	  could detect crawlers by ip adress and later we could detect
	  crawlers by analysing automatically the session table

2007-09-13 15:12  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/Auth.pm: [#3183][] Fix: Trusted application name check
	  was case sensitive, xhreas it is not supposed to be the case.
	  Fixed by lowercasing comparison in remote_app_check_password().

2007-09-13 14:23  david.verdin

	* src/Language.pm: [#3269][Submitted by J. stman, Helsinki univ.
	  of technology] Fix: sympa would take the LANGUAGE environment
	  variable as its default instead of its lang parameter value,
	  because this is Gettext default behaviour.

2007-09-13 14:14  david.verdin

	* src/tools.pl, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Reinstantiating the XSS
	  regexp protection.

2007-09-13 13:41  david.verdin

	* src/Conf.pm: [requested by JM.Martins da Cruz] Added X-Sympa-To
	  and X-Family-To header fields to those header that should be
	  removed by Sympa for outgoing mails

2007-09-13 10:24  david.verdin

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Change: make the 'body' parameter required
	  while composing a message. This is especially usefull because the
	  XSS code may erase the body parameter.

2007-09-13 09:24  david.verdin

	* web_tt2/home.tt2: [Change:] Moved the search list form to the top
	  of the Sympa home page.

2007-09-11 15:34  david.verdin

	* Makefile.am, Makefile.in, configure, configure.in,
	  src/sympa_wizard.pl, wwsympa/Makefile, wwsympa/wwslib.pm,
	  wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [Change] icons are now included in the
	  sympa static content directory. Consequently, the
	  "--with-iconsdir" configure option and the "icons_url"
	  wwsympa.conf parameter are no longer used. The default path to
	  icons is now {sympa home}/static_content/icons and the default
	  icons URL is http://host/icons/.

2007-09-10 15:37  david.verdin

	* src/Conf.pm, src/Family.pm, src/List.pm, wwsympa/bounce-lib.pl:
	  [#3271][Reported by M. Anderson, riseup.net] Fix: "$/" value was
	  changed in several places without using a proper "local" operator
	  to prevent system-wide field seperator contamination.

