	* src/Log.pm: Added a get_log_level() sub

2007-07-31 14:47  olivier.salaun

	* soap/sympa_soap_server.fcgi, src/Log.pm,
	  src/etc/script/testlogs.pl, src/sympa.pl, src/task_manager.pl,
	  wwsympa/archived.pl, wwsympa/bounced.pl, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi:
	  Change: turned $log_level into a class variable

2007-07-31 14:18  olivier.salaun

	* src/Log.pm: Optimized do_log to return earlier if log_level is
	  low

2007-07-31 14:18  olivier.salaun

	* ChangeLog: updated

2007-07-30 13:16  olivier.salaun

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Fixed log to remove regexp parameter

2007-07-30 13:07  olivier.salaun

	* wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [reported by Alessio] Fix: a security
	  problem would allow a user to directly access arctxt/* files or
	  .mhonarc.db files. A %in_negative_regexp hash has been added to
	  define forbidden expressions in parameters. XSS-related code has
	  also been changed.

2007-07-03 17:48  david.verdin

	* src/tools.pl, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: [#2960][Reported by L.
	  Ren-Shan] Fix: First attempt at XSS prevention. Now prevents such
	  intrusions in the web interface.

2007-07-02 09:50  david.verdin

	* soap/sympa_soap_client.pl, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Fix:
	  sympa_soap_client.pl now takes into account the "--service" and
	  "--service_parameter" arguments for "play_soap()" function.

2007-06-29 15:26  david.verdin

	* src/Family.pm, src/admin.pm: Fix: config files generated by
	  instantiate_family were not UTF-8 but ISO. Now opening files as
	  UTF-8.

2007-06-28 15:20  olivier.salaun

	* src/List.pm, src/mail.pm: Fix: use 'warning' log level instead of
	  'warn'

2007-06-28 08:41  david.verdin

	* soap/sympasoap.pm, src/Commands.pm, src/List.pm,
	  wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi: Feature: removes "sync_include" task when a
	  synchronization is triggered by another event than task
	  processing.
	  Feature: review actions on list using includes trigger a user's
	  list synchronization.

2007-06-26 16:08  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm: Feature: When sending a message, Sympa now checks
	  whether the last include is older than ttl OR distribute_ttl if
	  this one is defined. If it is, sychronization is done.

2007-06-26 15:29  david.verdin

	* src/List.pm: Feature: Added distribution_ttl parameter which will
	  be used when an action should check if a sync_include is needed
	  prior to be executed.

2007-06-26 14:19  olivier.salaun

	* check_perl_modules.pl: Sympa requires Perl 5.8 (for encoding
	  features)

2007-06-26 14:10  olivier.salaun

	* INSTALL: Updated install instructions

2007-06-26 13:34  olivier.salaun

	* ChangeLog: Updated Changelog

2007-06-26 13:20  olivier.salaun

	* soap/sympasoap.pm, src/List.pm, src/Upgrade.pm,
	  src/etc/script/arc2webarc.pl, src/etc/script/mod2html.pl,
	  src/etc/script/p12topem.pl, src/sympa.pl, src/task_manager.pl,
	  wwsympa/archived.pl, wwsympa/bounced.pl, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi:
	  Change: now set List::use_db in Upgrade::Probe_db() and
	  List::check_db_connect() to prevent "Sympa not setup for DBI"
	  errors.

2007-06-20 15:22  david.verdin

	* soap/sympasoap.pm: Added the following comment :
	  This test's purpose is to ensure that we are presented the right
	  cookie. In addition, we avoid the following problem: if the
	  cookie is composed of digits only ([0-9]) AND it starts with at
	  least one zero character, it is treated as a number and the
	  leading zeros are ignored. When tested against checksum, it is
	  not the same character string as the leading zeros are missing.
	  We add a number comparison to avoid it. Example: 00785136 becomes
	  785136.

2007-06-20 15:00  david.verdin

	* soap/sympasoap.pm: Fix: Yet another ( better ) solution to remove
	  the forged cookie problem.

2007-06-20 14:08  david.verdin

	* soap/sympasoap.pm: Fix: Avoid potentially forged cookie from SOAP
	  client.

2007-06-20 12:32  david.verdin

	* soap/sympasoap.pm: [Reported by P. David, univ. Strasbourg] Fix:
	  In some very rare occurences, the session identifier would be
	  constituted of decimal numbers only AND start with at least one
	  "0" (zero) character. In this case, this string was considered a
	  number by sympasoap.pm and the zero removed, thus shortening -
	  and invalidating - the id. This would prevent the user from being
	  authorized to see pages in the wiki.

2007-06-20 07:30  olivier.salaun

	* check_perl_modules.pl: [reported by S.Hornburg] Change: remove
	  unuseful dependency for Crypt::OpenSSL::X50 perl module. It was
	  introduced in revision 3754.

2007-06-19 14:34  david.verdin

	* src/task_manager.pl: [#3142][submitted by Y. BLUSSEAU] Fix: A
	  typo made the stop() command fail to remove tasks.

2007-06-19 13:39  olivier.salaun

	* wwsympa/wwslib.pm: [#2931][A.GAVARA, INPL Nancy] Fix: CAS
	  authentication would fail because http was used instead of https.
	  Fixed get_my_url() to use HTTPS environment variable instead of
	  SSL_PROTOCOL and SSL_PROTOCOL_VERSION.

2007-06-13 07:53  david.verdin

	* .version, ChangeLog, NEWS: Preparing new version 5.3.2

