2006-08-11 12:30  olivier.salaun

	* doc/sympa.tex.tpl, mail_tt2/listmaster_notification.tt2,
	  src/Conf.pm, src/Language.pm, src/List.pm,
	  src/etc/mhonarc-ressources.tt2, src/tt2.pl, web_tt2/arc.tt2,
	  web_tt2/main.tt2, web_tt2/tt2_error.tt2, wwsympa/wwsympa.fcgi:
	  ***** Changes: web pages are now utf-8 encoded, as well as
	  mhonarc HTML
	  ***** archives that can now mix different character sets within a
	  single
	  ***** web archive. Sympa now uses perl's I/O layer to
	  encode/decode characters.
	  ***** The web_recode_to parameter is now obsolete ; the new
	  ***** filesystem_encoding parameter allows you defining how the
	  configuration
	  ***** files are encoded on disk. A new mhonarc-ressources.tt2
	  file is provided
	  ***** and should replace any custom one.

